\title{\textbf{\textcolor{primary}{InterviewMate AI}}\\[0.3cm]
\Large An Intelligent AI-Powered Mock Interview Platform with\\Real-time Emotion Analysis and Confidence Scoring}
\author{Project Team}
\date{Academic Year 2025-2026}

\begin{document}
\maketitle

\begin{abstract}
\noindent
\textbf{InterviewMate AI} is an advanced mock interview platform that leverages Artificial Intelligence to transform how candidates prepare for job interviews. The system combines \textbf{computer vision}, \textbf{natural language processing}, and \textbf{speech analysis} to provide comprehensive, real-time feedback during simulated interview sessions.

The platform features a \textbf{React.js frontend} with an intuitive user interface, a \textbf{Python Flask backend} powered by multiple AI modules, and a \textbf{MySQL/MongoDB database} for persistent storage. Key innovations include:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{AI Question Generation:} LLM-based dynamic question generation tailored to resume content, job category (15+ domains), and target company (TCS, Infosys, Wipro, Accenture, etc.)
    \item \textbf{Facial Emotion Detection:} Real-time analysis of facial expressions using OpenCV and CNN models to detect confidence, nervousness, and engagement levels
    \item \textbf{Speech Emotion Recognition:} Audio analysis using Librosa and ML classifiers to detect vocal stress, enthusiasm, and clarity
    \item \textbf{STAR Model Compliance:} Automated evaluation of answers against the Situation-Task-Action-Result framework
    \item \textbf{Confidence Score Engine:} Weighted multi-factor scoring combining facial, speech, NLP, and eye-contact metrics
    \item \textbf{Real-time Feedback:} Live tips and suggestions during the interview session
    \item \textbf{Comprehensive Reports:} Detailed post-session reports with charts, improvement tips, and PDF export
    \item \textbf{Progress Tracking:} Longitudinal performance analytics with trend visualization
\end{itemize}

The system addresses the critical gap in interview preparation by providing objective, data-driven insights that help candidates identify weaknesses, improve communication skills, and build confidence before actual interviews.

\vspace{0.5cm}
\noindent\textbf{Keywords:} Artificial Intelligence, Mock Interview, Emotion Recognition, Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Confidence Scoring, STAR Model, Flask, React.js, Deep Learning
\end{abstract}

